WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.376 --> 00:00:03.170
["Hey Mami" plays]

2
00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:11.219
Hi. I'm picking up for Paula Sanders.

3
00:00:11.220 --> 00:00:12.679
[mouthing words] Okay.

4
00:00:17.392 --> 00:00:18.602
Nice font.

5
00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:26.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

6
00:00:45.712 --> 00:00:46.713
Yeah.

7
00:00:49.466 --> 00:00:50.676
[music ends]

8
00:01:08.777 --> 00:01:11.446
[car engine rumbles]

9
00:01:13.699 --> 00:01:16.242
- [Rudy sighs]
- We're at twelve percent. Paula.

10
00:01:16.243 --> 00:01:18.160
She's still driving. What do you wanna do?

11
00:01:18.161 --> 00:01:20.705
[Paula] <i>Oh. God. I wanna slice my wrists
with a pizza cutter.</i>

12
00:01:20.706 --> 00:01:23.040
What the hell is "gluten reduced"?

13
00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:26.210
If a lot of gluten kills you.
does a little less make you blind?

14
00:01:26.211 --> 00:01:28.754
Focus. The woman in the motel
called the killer. right?

15
00:01:28.755 --> 00:01:30.840
If we can somehow find her phone.
then maybe we can find him.

16
00:01:30.841 --> 00:01:33.217
Yeah. Forget about
your stupid pizza party. okay?

17
00:01:33.218 --> 00:01:35.094
Which neither of us
were invited to. by the way.

18
00:01:35.095 --> 00:01:38.097
If you were eight and play center-mid.
then you would've been invited.

19
00:01:38.098 --> 00:01:39.641
And it isn't actually… Ooh!

20
00:01:40.434 --> 00:01:43.269
This "stupid party"
is actually really important

21
00:01:43.270 --> 00:01:45.229
because I really need it to go well.

22
00:01:45.230 --> 00:01:47.690
so that everyone raves
about what an amazing mom I am.

23
00:01:47.691 --> 00:01:51.611
so that… [stammers] …Karl can't move
my daughter to Sasquatch country.

24
00:01:51.612 --> 00:01:53.404
- [computer chimes]
- [Geri] Eleven percent.

25
00:01:53.405 --> 00:01:55.489
Oh. the two of you are stressing me out.

26
00:01:55.490 --> 00:01:56.908
I'm getting stomach bubbles.
I can feel it.

27
00:01:56.909 --> 00:01:58.284
What if we divide and conquer?

28
00:01:58.285 --> 00:01:59.702
Great. yeah. That's a great idea.

29
00:01:59.703 --> 00:02:01.287
You go to a nice party with cute kids.

30
00:02:01.288 --> 00:02:03.289
and Geri and I will track down
a dangerous lunatic.

31
00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:05.709
- Seems fair. Wait. shit. that's perfect.
- We will go.

32
00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:08.418
Thank you. Thank you. thank you so much.

33
00:02:08.419 --> 00:02:11.548
I-I-I mean. this is the only lead we have.
and-and-and I…

34
00:02:13.050 --> 00:02:15.260
I honestly couldn't do this
without you. guys.

35
00:02:16.845 --> 00:02:17.846
[whispers] Be safe.

36
00:02:18.931 --> 00:02:21.766
- Come on. Let's go.
- I don't like being pressured. okay?

37
00:02:21.767 --> 00:02:24.810
My therapist actually says I have
a touch of oppositional defiant disorder.

38
00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:27.063
Pressuring me makes me
want to do the opposite.

39
00:02:27.064 --> 00:02:28.981
Great. Don't hurry the fuck up.

40
00:02:28.982 --> 00:02:31.401
Ha. ha. ha.
Doesn't work like that. [scoffs]

41
00:02:32.236 --> 00:02:33.987
Yeah. actually. it kind of does.

42
00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:37.324
- Let's go.
- Good.

43
00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:40.160
[whirring]

44
00:03:05.978 --> 00:03:07.229
[upbeat music playing]

45
00:03:10.482 --> 00:03:11.483
[Dennis sighs]

46
00:03:30.502 --> 00:03:32.129
[exhales]

47
00:04:16.005 --> 00:04:17.089
[sighs]

48
00:04:39.154 --> 00:04:41.197
[Gonzales] Don't think anyone's home.

49
00:04:41.198 --> 00:04:44.617
[Baxter] The cam boy who owned the account
that paid for the construction supplies

50
00:04:44.618 --> 00:04:47.286
is chilling in the morgue.
so he's probably not here.

51
00:04:47.287 --> 00:04:49.289
[Gonzales] The sarcasm. It's off-putting.

52
00:04:50.207 --> 00:04:52.918
- You name that cat yet?
- Nah. nothing's sticking.

53
00:04:53.418 --> 00:04:54.710
Try Stella.

54
00:04:54.711 --> 00:04:56.504
[chuckles] Asshole.

55
00:04:56.505 --> 00:04:59.549
What? It'll only be awkward
if your ex came back.

56
00:04:59.550 --> 00:05:00.551
Chill.

57
00:05:01.051 --> 00:05:04.345
Really? You're so used to calling out
her name in the middle of the night

58
00:05:04.346 --> 00:05:05.639
and her not coming.

59
00:05:06.390 --> 00:05:09.642
Let's start upstairs. You lead.
I'll definitely have your back.

60
00:05:09.643 --> 00:05:11.186
[Gonzales] There's that sarcasm again.

61
00:05:18.569 --> 00:05:20.195
Ding-dong. NYPD.

62
00:05:24.032 --> 00:05:25.325
[eerie music plays]

63
00:05:35.002 --> 00:05:36.211
[lock rattles]

64
00:05:42.176 --> 00:05:43.385
[lock rattles]

65
00:05:47.723 --> 00:05:48.682
[whistles]

66
00:06:08.535 --> 00:06:10.037
Police. open up!

67
00:06:20.088 --> 00:06:21.465
[grunts]

68
00:06:22.049 --> 00:06:23.133
Got a body here.

69
00:06:25.302 --> 00:06:26.303
Room. right.

70
00:06:29.097 --> 00:06:30.766
- We're clear.
- Bathroom.

71
00:06:33.143 --> 00:06:34.144
Clear.

72
00:06:35.062 --> 00:06:36.063
[sighs]

73
00:06:42.653 --> 00:06:43.779
What the fuck?

74
00:06:50.619 --> 00:06:52.371
[clanking]

75
00:06:54.998 --> 00:06:56.124
Better call it in.

76
00:07:04.466 --> 00:07:06.218
[eerie music plays]

77
00:07:10.722 --> 00:07:13.641
- [Paula chuckles] Whoa. Oh. my gosh!
- He escaped from jail.

78
00:07:13.642 --> 00:07:15.977
- Yeah.
- Pull those balloons in. There you go.

79
00:07:15.978 --> 00:07:19.063
I was insanely hungry earlier.
and I was desperate

80
00:07:19.064 --> 00:07:21.941
because you didn't buy me anything
from the food court. Mom.

81
00:07:21.942 --> 00:07:23.901
- I couldn't carry all of it.
- I gotta pee.

82
00:07:23.902 --> 00:07:24.903
All right.

83
00:07:29.491 --> 00:07:30.492
[exhales]

84
00:07:32.369 --> 00:07:34.830
- [Hazel screaming] Oh. my God. Mom!
- Hazel.

85
00:07:36.164 --> 00:07:37.331
Hazel!

86
00:07:37.332 --> 00:07:38.333
[Hazel yelps]

87
00:07:39.251 --> 00:07:41.252
Baby. what-what-what happened?
Are you okay?

88
00:07:41.253 --> 00:07:42.254
[Hazel whimpers]

89
00:07:46.341 --> 00:07:47.593
Oh. God.

90
00:07:48.594 --> 00:07:51.680
Oh. my God. You scared me.

91
00:07:55.225 --> 00:07:56.392
[exclaims]

92
00:07:56.393 --> 00:07:57.936
[sucks teeth. blows raspberry]

93
00:07:58.520 --> 00:07:59.437
[grunts]

94
00:07:59.438 --> 00:08:01.607
- Mom! You killed it.
- [toilet flushes]

95
00:08:02.149 --> 00:08:04.859
You can't kill a cockroach. okay?

96
00:08:04.860 --> 00:08:07.403
It's probably down there
with a million of its friends. just like.

97
00:08:07.404 --> 00:08:09.280
plotting world domination. It's okay.

98
00:08:09.281 --> 00:08:10.948
A million?

99
00:08:10.949 --> 00:08:12.826
- [toilet seat bangs]
- Can they crawl up the toilet?

100
00:08:13.702 --> 00:08:16.330
[door closes. lock clicks]

101
00:08:32.554 --> 00:08:34.056
[beeping]

102
00:08:51.323 --> 00:08:53.242
[dramatic music plays]

103
00:09:01.792 --> 00:09:02.793
Okay.

104
00:09:03.544 --> 00:09:04.753
["Everything Is Litty" playing]

105
00:09:05.379 --> 00:09:07.798
[trills lips]

106
00:09:14.304 --> 00:09:16.055
Beautiful job. baby blue.

107
00:09:16.056 --> 00:09:17.099
Thank you.

108
00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:19.142
[knocks on door]

109
00:09:19.726 --> 00:09:20.727
[Paula] All right.

110
00:09:22.813 --> 00:09:24.397
- Okay. Hi. Oh.
- Hey.

111
00:09:24.398 --> 00:09:26.232
- Hazel.
- Oh. Silv…

112
00:09:26.233 --> 00:09:27.316
[Paula. Steve chuckle]

113
00:09:27.317 --> 00:09:29.527
[Steve] Sorry. sorry.
I know. I'm always early.

114
00:09:29.528 --> 00:09:31.654
You either find it endearing
or you divorce me.

115
00:09:31.655 --> 00:09:33.114
[both chuckle]

116
00:09:33.115 --> 00:09:34.950
Um. I thought you might need a hand.

117
00:09:35.534 --> 00:09:37.451
Or. uh. I could just drop Silvia off

118
00:09:37.452 --> 00:09:39.912
if this is more
of a mom-and-daughters-only.

119
00:09:39.913 --> 00:09:41.080
boys-got-cooties vibe?

120
00:09:41.081 --> 00:09:43.916
No. no. no. no. It's no problem.
I got the controversial cooties vaxx.

121
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:46.794
- So. uh. yeah. That would be amazing.
- Okay.

122
00:09:46.795 --> 00:09:48.505
Come on in. Yeah. I'm freaking out.

123
00:10:02.936 --> 00:10:06.439
Few things. We got some people to meet.
Karl. Mallory. this is Frank Budkins.

124
00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:09.317
He's the private investigator
working on your case.

125
00:10:09.318 --> 00:10:11.819
- Hi.
- We hired a private investigator?

126
00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:14.113
Yeah. It's my idea. Everyone hires a PI.

127
00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:16.240
- Everybody hires a PI?
- Yeah.

128
00:10:16.241 --> 00:10:18.743
Frank's very good. Just ask my ex-wife.

129
00:10:18.744 --> 00:10:21.412
She got half of everything
she thought I had. [chuckles]

130
00:10:21.413 --> 00:10:22.788
[Mallory chuckles]

131
00:10:22.789 --> 00:10:25.124
Uh. Frank. what do you got?

132
00:10:25.125 --> 00:10:28.044
Uh. for the past few days.
I've been surveilling Paula Sanders.

133
00:10:28.045 --> 00:10:30.880
Watching her house.
So far. there's not much.

134
00:10:30.881 --> 00:10:33.050
No drug use or heavy drinking.

135
00:10:35.219 --> 00:10:36.428
She works.

136
00:10:37.513 --> 00:10:39.848
Shops. Coaches soccer.

137
00:10:40.349 --> 00:10:42.517
- In bed by 11:00.
- So that's it?

138
00:10:42.518 --> 00:10:45.269
She didn't talk to anyone strange?
No weird run-ins?

139
00:10:45.270 --> 00:10:46.521
I wasn't done yet.

140
00:10:46.522 --> 00:10:49.066
Looks like there's a new boyfriend
in the picture.

141
00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:52.402
Uh. this man was alone
in Paula's apartment today.

142
00:10:53.070 --> 00:10:56.239
I'm going back later.
I'll try and get a clearer picture.

143
00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:59.367
I'm guessing it's serious enough.
He has a key.

144
00:10:59.368 --> 00:11:00.743
- What the fuck?
- What?

145
00:11:00.744 --> 00:11:04.038
- Did she mention a new boyfriend to you?
- No. she hasn't told me anything.

146
00:11:04.039 --> 00:11:06.082
- [scoffs]
- It's hard to see what he looks like.

147
00:11:06.083 --> 00:11:09.752
She should not be giving some random guy
the key to your daughter's home.

148
00:11:09.753 --> 00:11:11.128
- No.
- Look. the good news is.

149
00:11:11.129 --> 00:11:14.048
- this can only help strengthen our case.
- [Karl] Strengthen our case?

150
00:11:14.049 --> 00:11:16.884
Look. I didn't go to law school.
but how is this not a slam dunk?

151
00:11:16.885 --> 00:11:19.595
The backboard should shatter.
This should be on ESPN.

152
00:11:19.596 --> 00:11:21.806
This is like varsity
versus junior varsity.

153
00:11:21.807 --> 00:11:23.641
- This is obvious.
- [Mallory] Okay.

154
00:11:23.642 --> 00:11:26.436
This is a skunk.
How could we not fucking win this case?

155
00:11:27.855 --> 00:11:30.690
I'm feeling very good
about our chances. okay?

156
00:11:30.691 --> 00:11:33.192
Can you give me a second?
I just wanna focus on something here.

157
00:11:33.193 --> 00:11:34.194
Okay.

158
00:11:36.321 --> 00:11:38.489
- What's going on with you?
- Nothing. Nothing.

159
00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:40.908
- You've been very edgy…
- It's a stressful moment. I know.

160
00:11:40.909 --> 00:11:41.910
…the last couple days.

161
00:11:42.911 --> 00:11:44.580
Well. uh… Well. there's. um…

162
00:11:46.123 --> 00:11:47.666
- [sighs]
- What?

163
00:11:48.792 --> 00:11:50.042
It's nothing.

164
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:51.545
- [stammers]
- [Mallory] Okay.

165
00:11:52.296 --> 00:11:54.047
I just over-caffeinated.

166
00:11:54.840 --> 00:11:59.010
Yeah. I had. uh. two double espressos.
so I quadruple espressoed.

167
00:11:59.011 --> 00:12:01.888
You're too old for that.
Don't do that anymore.

168
00:12:01.889 --> 00:12:04.307
Okay. let me just walk you guys
through the hearings. okay?

169
00:12:04.308 --> 00:12:08.311
It's great that we got. uh. Narleski.
but I don't wanna rest on our laurels.

170
00:12:08.312 --> 00:12:10.021
I wanna make sure
this is bulletproof. okay?

171
00:12:10.022 --> 00:12:12.107
So. let's just talk through
the paperwork. all right?

172
00:12:13.150 --> 00:12:15.067
We got the letter from the school board.

173
00:12:15.068 --> 00:12:16.652
We got bank statements.

174
00:12:16.653 --> 00:12:19.238
I need a bank statement from you. Karl.
You got that?

175
00:12:19.239 --> 00:12:21.157
- I need a job offer from you. all right?
- [Mallory] Mm-hmm.

176
00:12:21.158 --> 00:12:22.700
- [Scott] Can you get that to me?
- Yeah.

177
00:12:22.701 --> 00:12:24.660
[Scott distorted] Good. Uh…
Oh. And I'm going to set you up

178
00:12:24.661 --> 00:12:28.289
with a child psychiatrist.
She is fantastic.

179
00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:30.375
- [speaks indistinctly]
- [dramatic music plays]

180
00:12:33.420 --> 00:12:36.047
Whoa! That is some serious chopping.

181
00:12:36.048 --> 00:12:37.882
You know. I was once on <i>Chopped</i>.

182
00:12:37.883 --> 00:12:39.342
What? Really?

183
00:12:39.343 --> 00:12:43.387
Yeah. Not as a contestant.
but. uh. I was in the audience.

184
00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:45.264
Okay. that's not true either.

185
00:12:45.265 --> 00:12:47.267
I've never actually
even watched <i>Chopped</i>. I lied.

186
00:12:50.687 --> 00:12:52.355
But you did it to impress me.

187
00:12:52.356 --> 00:12:55.150
- Oh. no. It's pathological.
- [Paula chuckles]

188
00:12:56.068 --> 00:12:59.612
Oh. you know what?
You should use the sharp knife.

189
00:12:59.613 --> 00:13:02.573
- You got a sharp knife?
- I do. I have a Früsthof.

190
00:13:02.574 --> 00:13:03.699
I used to have a Früsthof.

191
00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:06.619
- Yeah? You lost it in the divorce?
- Mm-hmm. Yeah.

192
00:13:06.620 --> 00:13:08.746
Mmm. At least I kept the Nutribullet.

193
00:13:08.747 --> 00:13:10.206
Not that I ever use it.

194
00:13:10.207 --> 00:13:11.999
The important thing
is that she doesn't get to use it.

195
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:13.001
That's right.

196
00:13:14.002 --> 00:13:15.378
[both chuckle]

197
00:13:15.379 --> 00:13:17.380
I don't know where this knife is.

198
00:13:17.381 --> 00:13:18.464
[knocks on door]

199
00:13:18.465 --> 00:13:19.674
Oh. party's starting.

200
00:13:19.675 --> 00:13:21.425
- I should get out of your hair.
- Yeah.

201
00:13:21.426 --> 00:13:22.677
Sorry for the mess.

202
00:13:22.678 --> 00:13:24.136
Okay.

203
00:13:24.137 --> 00:13:25.138
Bye. honey!

204
00:13:26.181 --> 00:13:27.348
Um. thank you.

205
00:13:27.349 --> 00:13:29.726
- Yeah. of course. Yeah… Oh.
- Yeah. All right.

206
00:13:33.188 --> 00:13:34.606
[knocks on door]

207
00:13:35.274 --> 00:13:36.441
[Steve exhales]

208
00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:40.319
- Hey! Have so much fun. you two.
- Yeah!

209
00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:42.613
- [Paula] Hi. everybody.
- [Steve] Oh. hi!

210
00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:44.866
- [cheering]
- [Steve] Oh. okay. All right. excuse me.

211
00:13:44.867 --> 00:13:45.950
All right.

212
00:13:45.951 --> 00:13:47.368
- This is for you.
- [Paula] Oh. wow! Thanks.

213
00:13:47.369 --> 00:13:48.452
[mouthing words] Good luck.

214
00:13:48.453 --> 00:13:51.330
- [kid 1] Hi.
- [chuckles] Steve in the house. huh?

215
00:13:51.331 --> 00:13:52.957
- Yes.
- [Kyra smacks lips]

216
00:13:52.958 --> 00:13:54.292
- [Steve grunting]
- [Paula] Hey.

217
00:13:54.293 --> 00:13:55.794
I brought too much wine.

218
00:14:01.175 --> 00:14:02.342
[Geri exhales]

219
00:14:03.260 --> 00:14:04.635
It says we're right on top of it.

220
00:14:04.636 --> 00:14:06.929
Our dot and that dot
are basically one dot.

221
00:14:06.930 --> 00:14:07.931
Where is it?

222
00:14:11.643 --> 00:14:12.769
[Geri] There.

223
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:14.687
[Rudy] Yeah.

224
00:14:14.688 --> 00:14:16.772
Where you going? What… What's going on?

225
00:14:16.773 --> 00:14:19.609
Hey. hey. Damn it. Slow down.

226
00:14:19.610 --> 00:14:21.485
Why? It's at 3%.

227
00:14:21.486 --> 00:14:24.071
It's gonna die. and then we're
not gonna have another chance.

228
00:14:24.072 --> 00:14:25.908
[suspenseful music playing]

229
00:14:28.160 --> 00:14:29.161
Huh.

230
00:14:31.580 --> 00:14:33.289
Hey. reach in there and unlock it.

231
00:14:33.290 --> 00:14:35.875
- You reach in there and unlock it.
- No. your arms are crazy long.

232
00:14:35.876 --> 00:14:38.419
My arms are normal.
These are normal man arms.

233
00:14:38.420 --> 00:14:40.630
You're a fucking giant
with a freakish wingspan.

234
00:14:40.631 --> 00:14:43.424
So stick those pool noodles in there
and unlock the door. Go.

235
00:14:43.425 --> 00:14:44.426
[Rudy exhales]

236
00:14:48.096 --> 00:14:49.514
[barks]

237
00:14:49.515 --> 00:14:51.057
- Oh. shit.
- Oh. my God.

238
00:14:51.058 --> 00:14:53.601
- [dog yelps]
- [Rudy grunts] Oh.

239
00:14:53.602 --> 00:14:55.144
Fucking shit dog.

240
00:14:55.145 --> 00:14:57.230
Who even leaves a dog in a car like that?

241
00:14:57.231 --> 00:14:58.857
Hi. princess.

242
00:14:59.358 --> 00:15:01.526
Aw. [chuckles]

243
00:15:01.527 --> 00:15:02.860
I hope it chews your lips off.

244
00:15:02.861 --> 00:15:04.446
Can you get in there
and look for the phone?

245
00:15:13.705 --> 00:15:15.791
- Hurry!
- I'm looking. I'm looking. I'm looking.

246
00:15:16.416 --> 00:15:18.043
No. Oh.

247
00:15:18.669 --> 00:15:20.963
- Did you find it?
- Bing-fucking-go.

248
00:15:21.547 --> 00:15:23.131
[sighs] Come on. Okay.

249
00:15:24.383 --> 00:15:25.384
Come on.

250
00:15:26.301 --> 00:15:27.802
[Geri] Okay. Go. Okay.

251
00:15:27.803 --> 00:15:29.595
Wait. wait. wait. wait. My earbud.

252
00:15:29.596 --> 00:15:32.223
No. no. no. no. She'll be out any second.
I also probably have rabies.

253
00:15:32.224 --> 00:15:35.018
I need. like. a dozen shots in my stomach.
or I'll be frothing at the mouth.

254
00:15:35.978 --> 00:15:36.979
[kids laughing. chattering]

255
00:15:38.105 --> 00:15:39.523
[chuckles]

256
00:15:42.901 --> 00:15:45.528
[exclaiming]

257
00:15:45.529 --> 00:15:47.948
Did you see that?
The balloon just flew away.

258
00:15:49.449 --> 00:15:51.493
Hey. Whoa. whoa. whoa.

259
00:15:53.704 --> 00:15:56.163
I'm back. I'm coming back with the red.

260
00:15:56.164 --> 00:15:58.457
Oh. Fantastic cheese-to-sauce ratio.

261
00:15:58.458 --> 00:15:59.542
- Good job.
- [chuckles]

262
00:15:59.543 --> 00:16:03.838
All right. chicken. sausage and M&M'S.
Oh. you're definitely gonna throw up.

263
00:16:03.839 --> 00:16:06.716
Oh. uh. Emily. I think your mom said
that you're vegetarian.

264
00:16:06.717 --> 00:16:09.427
- You're eating pepperoni.
- Pepperoni is made out of peppers.

265
00:16:09.428 --> 00:16:11.012
That's a common misconception.

266
00:16:11.013 --> 00:16:13.222
[stutters] Why don't you use this instead?

267
00:16:13.223 --> 00:16:16.225
- [kid] Oh. no!
- Oh. Uh. big spill.

268
00:16:16.226 --> 00:16:17.644
- [Paula] Oops.
- Do you have a towel?

269
00:16:20.689 --> 00:16:22.982
That's okay. You know. I hate this rug.

270
00:16:22.983 --> 00:16:25.569
You did me a favor. All right.

271
00:16:26.612 --> 00:16:28.779
Oh… [mutters] What a disaster. [chuckles]

272
00:16:28.780 --> 00:16:32.159
Are you kidding me?
Look how much fun they're having.

273
00:16:32.868 --> 00:16:36.871
I may be a little buzzed.
but I think you're nailing this.

274
00:16:36.872 --> 00:16:39.708
They still have to eat.
We're not out of the woods yet.

275
00:16:40.334 --> 00:16:42.085
What? You're doing great.

276
00:16:43.545 --> 00:16:45.464
[kids chattering. screaming]

277
00:16:46.131 --> 00:16:47.132
[elevator dings]

278
00:16:49.593 --> 00:16:50.968
[lover 1 moans]

279
00:16:50.969 --> 00:16:51.970
[both chuckle]

280
00:16:55.933 --> 00:16:57.768
Oh. hey. Don't let me stop you.

281
00:16:58.685 --> 00:16:59.937
[both chuckle]

282
00:17:00.521 --> 00:17:04.733
"Gather ye rose-buds while ye may.
old time is still a-flying.

283
00:17:05.692 --> 00:17:10.030
And the same flower that smiles today.
tomorrow will be dying."

284
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:15.035
Life is short. Shit happens.

285
00:17:15.618 --> 00:17:17.870
[smacks lips] Um. sure. Thanks.

286
00:17:17.871 --> 00:17:20.457
Oh. you're young. You'll see.

287
00:17:22.835 --> 00:17:24.919
Cool. [chuckles]

288
00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:28.506
The only thing that makes the misery
and horror of life worthwhile

289
00:17:28.507 --> 00:17:30.342
is kissing the person you love.

290
00:17:32.052 --> 00:17:32.970
So…

291
00:17:35.973 --> 00:17:36.974
Go on then.

292
00:17:39.601 --> 00:17:40.602
Kiss.

293
00:17:41.186 --> 00:17:42.979
[stammers] What?

294
00:17:42.980 --> 00:17:44.772
- Kiss.
- [lover 1 gulps]

295
00:17:44.773 --> 00:17:47.651
[heartbeat thumping]

296
00:17:49.820 --> 00:17:50.821
[chuckles]

297
00:17:52.823 --> 00:17:54.241
[elevator dings]

298
00:17:55.534 --> 00:17:58.620
- I'm joking. [chuckles]
- Oh. [chuckles]

299
00:18:00.330 --> 00:18:03.917
[chuckles] Don't forget
to gather those rosebuds!

300
00:18:10.841 --> 00:18:12.133
Shmooey.

301
00:18:12.134 --> 00:18:13.135
Hazel forgot him.

302
00:18:13.635 --> 00:18:16.387
Aw. and you wanted to spare me
the nuclear holocaust

303
00:18:16.388 --> 00:18:18.599
that is bedtime without Shmooey.
Thank you.

304
00:18:19.808 --> 00:18:21.101
You wanna have some pizza?

305
00:18:21.643 --> 00:18:23.060
[stutters] I made it myself.

306
00:18:23.061 --> 00:18:26.272
I can't promise you that it's good.
but there are flavor combos

307
00:18:26.273 --> 00:18:27.773
that you have never tried before.

308
00:18:27.774 --> 00:18:28.858
I'm all set.

309
00:18:28.859 --> 00:18:30.360
[chuckles]

310
00:18:30.861 --> 00:18:33.362
- What… What the heck?
- What the heck. what?

311
00:18:33.363 --> 00:18:35.489
What are you doing your angry walk for?

312
00:18:35.490 --> 00:18:38.368
I don't know. maybe 'cause
I got called into the police station.

313
00:18:39.161 --> 00:18:41.913
Yeah. apparently. you're mixed up
in the death of a gigolo.

314
00:18:41.914 --> 00:18:43.831
So. maybe that's why
I'm doing my angry walk.

315
00:18:43.832 --> 00:18:47.376
- A gigolo? [scoffs]
- Sorry. a male sex worker was unalived.

316
00:18:47.377 --> 00:18:49.587
and you have something to do with it.
Is that better?

317
00:18:49.588 --> 00:18:53.382
No. I don't. I don't. okay?

318
00:18:53.383 --> 00:18:56.886
It's a big misunderstanding. and-and.
honestly. it's none of your business.

319
00:18:56.887 --> 00:18:59.431
That's wrong. It is my business
'cause they called me in.

320
00:19:00.516 --> 00:19:03.602
You wanna know what the first thing
they asked me about was Portland.

321
00:19:05.270 --> 00:19:07.980
Now. luckily for you.
they only wanted me and not Mallory.

322
00:19:07.981 --> 00:19:09.482
who I had to lie to

323
00:19:09.483 --> 00:19:12.568
because if she knew
I was called into the station

324
00:19:12.569 --> 00:19:14.612
and she knew what they were asking about.

325
00:19:14.613 --> 00:19:16.448
I don't know what she would do.

326
00:19:17.115 --> 00:19:19.825
Well. like I said. it's just a…
It's-It's no big deal.

327
00:19:19.826 --> 00:19:22.704
And it's just a big dumb misunderstanding.

328
00:19:23.705 --> 00:19:25.499
Dumb misunderstanding.

329
00:19:28.001 --> 00:19:31.921
Is it also a dumb misunderstanding
that you gave keys

330
00:19:31.922 --> 00:19:33.756
- to your new boyfriend?
- What-What?

331
00:19:33.757 --> 00:19:35.508
I don't care what you do. I really don't.

332
00:19:35.509 --> 00:19:39.595
But if you're doling out keys
to where my daughter sleeps.

333
00:19:39.596 --> 00:19:41.264
then I deserve to know.

334
00:19:41.265 --> 00:19:44.183
I legit don't know
what you're talking about?

335
00:19:44.184 --> 00:19:47.019
- Stop lying to...
- I'm not seeing anyone.

336
00:19:47.020 --> 00:19:49.480
I saw the photos of him.

337
00:19:49.481 --> 00:19:52.484
- [chuckles] What are you talking about?
- We hired a private investigator.

338
00:19:53.110 --> 00:19:54.443
You hired a what?

339
00:19:54.444 --> 00:19:57.154
Don't be a child. Everybody hires a PI.

340
00:19:57.155 --> 00:20:01.033
And I saw your boyfriend in your house
when you weren't there.

341
00:20:01.034 --> 00:20:03.786
I saw him sitting on your couch.
going through your fridge.

342
00:20:03.787 --> 00:20:05.329
just acting like he lived there.

343
00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:07.415
So who is he? How serious is it?

344
00:20:07.416 --> 00:20:10.377
That's-That's impossible
because nobody's been here.

345
00:20:11.044 --> 00:20:14.506
I saw the photos. He was in there. Paula.

346
00:20:15.924 --> 00:20:17.009
Fuck's sake.

347
00:20:22.848 --> 00:20:26.476
Whatever you're doing.
please. just do better.

348
00:20:30.731 --> 00:20:32.733
[dramatic music plays]

349
00:20:34.943 --> 00:20:36.361
- [Hazel] Mom!
- [Paula sniffles]

350
00:20:36.945 --> 00:20:38.446
Mom!

351
00:20:38.447 --> 00:20:42.617
- My heart pizza's ready for the oven.
- Oh. yeah. Okay. great.

352
00:20:42.618 --> 00:20:44.368
- [Hazel] Shmooey!
- Look who came. um…

353
00:20:44.369 --> 00:20:47.205
Hey. so. uh. I think you're gonna stay
at a friend's house tonight.

354
00:20:47.206 --> 00:20:48.748
- [Hazel] Yes!
- That all right?

355
00:20:48.749 --> 00:20:49.750
Yeah. great.

356
00:20:56.173 --> 00:20:58.175
[suspenseful music plays]

357
00:21:10.270 --> 00:21:11.271
[Dennis grunts]

358
00:21:43.053 --> 00:21:46.389
Death by expanding foam.
Fun. Who's the victim?

359
00:21:46.390 --> 00:21:47.640
We're working on it.

360
00:21:47.641 --> 00:21:48.891
I know you don't wanna hear this.

361
00:21:48.892 --> 00:21:51.394
but we think this is connected
to the Thorwald murder.

362
00:21:51.395 --> 00:21:55.314
You know. you get paid to clear bodies
off the board. not add more. right?

363
00:21:55.315 --> 00:21:57.358
Oh. wait. really? Wow.

364
00:21:57.359 --> 00:21:59.610
We must've gotten that backwards
at the academy.

365
00:21:59.611 --> 00:22:01.404
Which end of the gun
do the bullets come out of?

366
00:22:01.405 --> 00:22:03.114
You guys wanna be smart-asses. or…

367
00:22:03.115 --> 00:22:04.699
Jesus. Pete. we didn't kill the guy.

368
00:22:04.700 --> 00:22:07.411
Then catch who did. Okay?

369
00:22:08.203 --> 00:22:10.038
And stop being two assholes.

370
00:22:19.298 --> 00:22:21.966
We're looking for an outgoing call
on Tuesday afternoon.

371
00:22:21.967 --> 00:22:25.137
I really think I'd be much happier
with a dumb phone like this.

372
00:22:25.721 --> 00:22:29.057
I should get a dumb phone.
Calls and texts. that's all I need.

373
00:22:30.350 --> 00:22:33.060
Uber is super helpful. I guess.
And the step counter.

374
00:22:33.061 --> 00:22:35.647
So. calls. texts. Uber.
my step counter. That's it.

375
00:22:36.231 --> 00:22:39.942
[sniffs] Although did you know
the 10.000 steps thing is a myth?

376
00:22:39.943 --> 00:22:43.070
It goes back to the '60s. This Japanese
company was marketing a pedometer.

377
00:22:43.071 --> 00:22:46.699
and I guess the Japanese character
for ten thousand looks like a guy walking.

378
00:22:46.700 --> 00:22:49.202
- So. it's a not hard science. but…
- Found it.

379
00:22:49.203 --> 00:22:51.954
6:23. Tuesday. Right before Paula escaped.

380
00:22:51.955 --> 00:22:54.540
This is the killer's phone number.
This is him.

381
00:22:54.541 --> 00:22:57.210
- Or her. Could be her.
- Wow. Feminist of the year over here.

382
00:22:57.211 --> 00:22:58.878
- Paula said it was a guy.
- Right.

383
00:22:58.879 --> 00:23:00.213
Holy shit. I can't believe it.

384
00:23:00.214 --> 00:23:02.298
We actually found
the killer's phone number.

385
00:23:02.299 --> 00:23:03.383
[chuckles]

386
00:23:04.301 --> 00:23:07.053
- We make a pretty good team.
- Yeah. we really do.

387
00:23:07.054 --> 00:23:10.139
I hate to say it.
but I think we should high-five right now.

388
00:23:10.140 --> 00:23:12.141
- No. No.
- Yep. I'm gonna do it.

389
00:23:12.142 --> 00:23:14.645
- I'm gonna put my hand up.
- Uh-oh. Oh. no. You're right.

390
00:23:15.395 --> 00:23:17.147
- [Geri chuckles]
- Let's go. [chuckles]

391
00:23:18.607 --> 00:23:19.608
Wow.

392
00:23:21.360 --> 00:23:23.444
- [children chuckling]
- [Jessica sighs]

393
00:23:23.445 --> 00:23:25.154
Okay. we're going. We're going.

394
00:23:25.155 --> 00:23:26.989
[Paula] Oh. okay.

395
00:23:26.990 --> 00:23:28.784
- Bye.
- Get home safe.

396
00:23:30.452 --> 00:23:32.454
[eerie music plays]

397
00:23:37.668 --> 00:23:41.879
Mom. Prem's mom said it was okay
if I slept over at her house.

398
00:23:41.880 --> 00:23:43.172
- Oh. great. Awesome.
- [Hazel] Yeah.

399
00:23:43.173 --> 00:23:45.299
And we're gonna stay up till 1:00 a.m..
and we're gonna watch <i>Twilight</i>.

400
00:23:45.300 --> 00:23:46.676
It's a PG-13 movie.

401
00:23:46.677 --> 00:23:47.802
[Paula vocalizes]

402
00:23:47.803 --> 00:23:49.680
[Prem] Mom. Hazel's coming with us.

403
00:23:50.180 --> 00:23:51.806
Your pizza was so good. Mom.

404
00:23:51.807 --> 00:23:52.890
- Really?
- Yeah.

405
00:23:52.891 --> 00:23:55.394
It was better than Bellucci's. [chuckles]

406
00:23:56.144 --> 00:23:57.228
[groans]

407
00:23:57.229 --> 00:23:59.772
Hey. Ginny. are you okay? Oh. my God.

408
00:23:59.773 --> 00:24:01.899
I checked the whole allergy list.
I thought...

409
00:24:01.900 --> 00:24:03.234
No. No. i-it's my fault.

410
00:24:03.235 --> 00:24:05.194
I forgot to tell you
she has a pineapple thing.

411
00:24:05.195 --> 00:24:06.863
- [Paula] Oh.
- Do you have antihistamine?

412
00:24:06.864 --> 00:24:08.739
- That usually helps.
- Uh. no.

413
00:24:08.740 --> 00:24:10.449
But there is a bodega down the street.

414
00:24:10.450 --> 00:24:11.993
You can definitely just.
like. pop out there.

415
00:24:11.994 --> 00:24:14.912
- Mommy. it itches.
- Okay. let-let me get you a cold towel.

416
00:24:14.913 --> 00:24:16.747
- Can you go so I can deal?
- Oh.

417
00:24:16.748 --> 00:24:18.834
[Gwynn] Thank you so much.
You're a lifesaver. Paula.

418
00:24:20.502 --> 00:24:21.837
[Ginny crying]

419
00:24:22.337 --> 00:24:24.339
[eerie music plays]

420
00:24:35.726 --> 00:24:37.603
[police sirens wailing]

421
00:24:40.230 --> 00:24:42.356
- [dog barking]
- Oh!

422
00:24:42.357 --> 00:24:44.193
[car alarm blaring]

423
00:25:01.335 --> 00:25:03.629
[distorted audio]

424
00:25:10.594 --> 00:25:14.473
Everything locked up.
I just wanna shave. [groans]

425
00:25:36.411 --> 00:25:37.412
[car alarm dings]

426
00:25:42.543 --> 00:25:43.836
[Paula groans]

427
00:25:45.295 --> 00:25:46.839
[groaning]

428
00:25:49.466 --> 00:25:50.466
[Dennis groans]

429
00:25:50.467 --> 00:25:52.678
- [screams] Help! Help!
- [grunts]

430
00:26:00.060 --> 00:26:01.770
[grunts. panting]

431
00:26:08.569 --> 00:26:10.654
[inhales. exhales]

432
00:26:17.870 --> 00:26:18.871
[exhales]

433
00:27:20.724 --> 00:27:21.767
[sighs]

434
00:27:22.309 --> 00:27:23.685
[eerie music playing]

435
00:27:35.864 --> 00:27:38.158
[Paula panting]

436
00:27:48.085 --> 00:27:51.380
["The Governor's Dead" playing]

